   <abstract>1877 July 4 Anson Nelson, Nashville, Tenn., to J.G.M. Ramsey, Knoxville, Tenn. Account of the Historical Society meeting the previous day. Discussion of his friendship with Mrs. James K. Polk, his weekly visits to her and a description of a recent memento lost. Reference to a portrait of J.G.M. belonging to the state. Asks about J.G.M.&apos;s new book and gives news of a convention to be held there.</abstract>
